data.title: Bruce Jenner pictured with two supportive ex-wives as Kris stays quiet
data.meta_description: There certainly seems to be a divide among the camp of Bruce Jenner's ex wives. While Chrystie Scott and Linda Thompson continue to sing his praises, the silence from Kris Jenner is deafening.
data.text:
There certainly seems to be a divide among the camp of Bruce Jenner's ex wives.

While Chrystie Scott and Linda Thompson continue to sing his praises, Kris Jenner has yet to open up about his decision.

On Wednesday, Thompson posted a snap of Bruce with his arms around both her and his first wife Chrystie, with a link to the lengthy and glowing article she wrote for the Huffington Post about their lives together.

Scroll down for video

Meanwhile, besides a 'late' tweet sent amid the deluge of support following Bruce's tell-all interview on Friday, the only noise from Kris has been her argument with ABC as to whether or not she was contacted for comment ahead of the programme.

On Wednesday, Thompson posted the pic of the three on Instagram with the caption: 'It has been gently brought to my attention that I never personally shared the link to the Huffington Post abbreviated excerpt from my memoir in progress. So here it is. And thank you for your loving & kind response! #chrystiebruceandme.'

The article itself is a 4,300 word opus titled 'How Living With and Loving Bruce Jenner Changed My Life Forever.'

On Monday Bruce's first wife Chrystie opened up on Good Morning America about how she dutifully kept his secret but loved him nonetheless.

On Wednesday, an article by People quoted a Kardashian insider who said that while Kris was aware of Bruce's female tendencies, she believed they were 'a quirk'.

Kris 'never knew Bruce wanted to be a woman. She thought Bruce had a little quirk and he asked her to keep it a secret, so she did', the article claimed.

A Jenner insider also told the site that 'before Kris and Bruce got married, Kris assured his ex-wives that she knew about "the issue". She wanted them to know that she thought it was just a phase and that she could "fix" him.'

During Friday's two-hour interview with Diane Sawyer, in which the former Olympian revealed he was a woman in front of almost 17million viewers, the host read out two messages of support from wives number one and two.

Scott's statement read: 'Someone who has lived 65 years of his life as the wrong gender has every right to live the last quarter of his life as his authentic self. I support him and so hope the world can too. I pray for his happiness for the rest of his journey.'

Thompson's followed: 'Bruce has always had my loyalty, even if he wasn't aware of it. I support his courage and commitment to this new chapter of his life. My hope is that his transition will inspire others who struggle with their identities, and my prayer is that humanity has evolved and been educated enough to exercise kindness toward those we may perceive as 'different.''

Sawyer then added that wife number three Kris had chose not to provide a comment.

Since ABC and Kris have been embroiled in a row over whether she was asked or not

Most recently the 59-year old claimed producers only contacted her office 'for fact checking,' but she felt she couldn't 'respond' because she hadn't seen the show, according to an article on Tuesday by People.com.

But ABC News insisted they reached out to Kris 'more than once', while one insider ridiculed the notion the network would simply overlook asking her.

However when celebrity blogger Perez Hilton called her out for not providing comment on Twitter, she angrily lashed back claiming she and Bruce had watched the programme together.

Meanwhile Linda Thompson was sharing further fond memories about another of her exes: Elvis Presley.

The 64-year old dated The King for four years in the 70s shortly after he split from Priscilla Presley, and lived with him in his iconic Graceland home.

On Monday she took her and Bruce's sons Brandon and Brody, and Brody's girlfriend Kaitlynn on a private tour of the home she shared with the legendary singer, which she apparently helped partly design

'Such a nostalgic private tour of Graceland today. I got to share with @brandontjenner @brodyjenner & @kaitlynn_carter memories of Elvis,' she wrote in an Instagram caption of the four standing in the hallowed halls.

'I designed the stained glass peacocks leading into the music room, the climbing roses and "P" stained glass at the front door,''I also decorated the downstairs rooms, and the Jungle Room... All according to Elvis's unique taste, of course. Really rarefied memories were made at Graceland.'

She also shared a TBT snap of her and a karate-suited Elvis together.
